text: Ouichka Mosque (), is a Tunisian mosque located in the north of the medina of Tunis. It does not exist anymore.Mohamed Belkhodja, Tārīkh maʻālim al-tawḥīd fī al-qadīm wa-fī al-Jadīd, Tunis, al-Maṭbaʻah al-Tūnisīyah, 1939, 429 p == Localization== The mosque was located in Ibn Abi Dhiaf Street. == Etymology== Ouichka is a Spanish word that refers to a Tunisian family with Andalusian origins. == History== It was built after the arrival of the Andalusians. == References == Category:Mosques in Tunis
title: Ouichka Mosque
